'''Space Jam 2024''' is an event hosted on [[VRChat]], and organized by the National Space Society of Australia ''(NSSA)'' starting on March 1, 2024<ref>[https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/space-jam 'Come on and Join the Space Jam!'] posted via ''hello.vrchat.com'' on March 1, 2024; retrieved February 25, 2025</ref>.

==Jam and rewards==
===Timeline===
*'''Submission deadline:''' March 1 - April 5, 11:59 pm EST
*'''Winners announced:''' April 12
*'''VRChat feature:''' April 12 - April 26, aligning with International Day of Human Space Flight
*'''New Horizons Summit showcase:''' May 9
===Evaluation criteria===
*'''Creativity and Originality:''' Unleash innovative VR concepts that blend historic insights with futuristic visions within the theme of space exploration.
*'''Technical Execution:''' Showcase advanced technical skills through sophisticated VR experiences that demonstrate innovative use of VR technology and interactive design.
*'''Alignment with Theme:''' Projects should deeply engage with the theme of space exploration, showcasing creative interpretations and future possibilities.
*'''Community Service and Functionality:''' Develop functional, entertaining, or relaxation-focused projects that enhance social interaction and community engagement within VRChat.
*'''Optional Bonus:''' Projects compatible with both PC and Android will receive bonus points. However, judging will primarily assess the PC version of the worlds.

===Rewards===
First place of the Space Jam received $4,000 AUD. Second place received $2,500 AUD, and third place received $1,500 AUD. There were also three runner-ups, and three 'special mentions' that were showcased within VRChat. Each winner was also given the opportunity to showcase their project at the ''[https://events.humanitix.com/nhs-2024 New Horizons Summit]'' on May 9, 2024.
